The paper deals with system identification, which is a topic in control theory and falls under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category. The use of kernel-based methods and regularization techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. The focus on estimating initial conditions and the use of maximum likelihood and expectation-maximization methods suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing) categories.
